CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 24, 1961, pg. 24, reads: "For A Great Cause - Even though the turnout for the Maurice Stokes benefit at Syria Mosque was small, outstanding personalities from the field of entertainment turned out for the event. Left photo shows Eartha Kitt, who contributed her services free, arriving for the show.  Behind her is David McDonald, president of the United Steelworkers of America, AFL-CIO... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Eartha Kitt carrying poodle, and David McDonald, standing in hallway of Syria Mosque for Maurice Stokes benefit
